The paper focuses on machine learning formulations of inductive program synthesis, which involves using input-output examples to synthesize source code. This falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper proposes a domain-specific language for expressing program synthesis problems, which is similar to a probabilistic programming language. This falls under the category of programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also discusses the use of neural networks and graphical models for program synthesis, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of constraint solving from the programming languages community, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE) and systems and control (cs.SY).
